    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="355"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <head>No. 355.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Drummond</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-09-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 4, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 26th ultimo, in which you informed the Department of the
                    gracious intention of Her Majesty, on the breaking up of the arctic discovery
                    ship Resolute at Chatham dock-yard, to present to the President a writing-table,
                    made from the timbers of that vessel, in acknowledgment of the restoration of
                    the same in 1856, as a free gift to Her Majesty by the President and people of
                    the United States.</p>
                <pb facs="0626" n="526" xml:id="pg_526"/>
                <p>Observing, in reply, that the agreeable contents of your note will be made known
                    to the President on his return from the West, and that the port of New York will
                    be a convenient one at which to receive the gift, I profit by this occasion,
                    sir, to again assure you of my very high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN HAY,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
